### Problem01


A pushdown stack (or just a stack) is a collection that is based on the _____(0)\___ policy (choose from the following options). 

 **Choices:**

a. first - in - first - out

b. first - in - last - out

c. last - in - last - out

d. last - in - first - out

*Excerpt From Computer Science Sedgewick, Robert,Wayne, Kevin. This material may be protected by copyright.*
